msgstr "cthulhic"

#: ../../C/cthulhic.rst:7
msgid "/kthool´hik/, adj\\."
msgstr "/kthool´hik/, 形容詞"

#: ../../C/cthulhic.rst:9
msgid ""
"Having the nature of a Cthulhu, the horrific tentacled green monstrosity "
"from H.P. Lovecraft's seminal horror fiction. Cthulhu sends dreams that "
"drive men mad, feeds on the flesh of screaming victims rent limb from limb, "
"and is served by a cult of degenerates. Hackers think this describes large "
":ref:`proprietary` systems such as traditional :ref:`mainframe`\\s, "
"installations of SAP and Oracle, or rooms full of Windows servers remarkably"
" well, and the adjective is used casually. Compare :ref:`Shub-Internet` and "
":ref:`crawling-horror`\\."
msgstr ""
"H.P. "
"Lovecraftの独創的なホラー小説に出てくる、触手を持つ恐ろしい緑色の怪物、Cthulhu(クトゥルフ)の性質を持つ。Cthulhuは人を狂気に追いやる夢を送り、四肢を引き裂かれて絶叫する犠牲者の肉を食らい、堕落者のカルトに仕えられています。ハッカーは、これが伝統的な\\"
" :ref:`mainframe`\\ 、SAPやOracleのインストール、Windowsサーバーで埋め尽くされた部屋のような大規模な\\ "
":ref:`proprietary`\\ システムを驚くほどよく表していると考えており、この形容詞は気軽に使われます。\\ :ref:`Shub-"
"Internet`\\ と\\ :ref:`crawling-horror`\\ と比較せよ。"
